[size=12pt][b][color=#9370DB]Critical Sync Fix - "Stuck at 10,000 Blocks" Resolved[/color][/b][/size]

Users reported sync getting stuck at ~10,000 blocks with only 5 blocks/sec speed instead of 100+ blocks/sec. [b]Root cause found and fixed![/b]

[b]The Bug:[/b]
[code]
// BEFORE (broken):
// Peer filter required height >= network_height (789,000)
// But peers at 258,495 and 449,976 were REJECTED
// Even though they had blocks the user needed!

filter: *height >= network_height  // ❌ Too strict!
[/code]

[b]The Fix:[/b]
[code]
// AFTER (v2.2.1):
// Accept ANY peer with blocks we need (height > current_height)

filter: *height > current_height  // ✅ Correct!
[/code]

This fix was applied to [b]3 locations[/b]:
[list]
[li][font=monospace]main.rs:10057-10079[/font] - Peer eligibility filter[/li]
[li][font=monospace]main.rs:10099-10104[/font] - Test peers filter[/li]
[li][font=monospace]turbo_sync.rs:1791-1837[/font] - Peer discovery function[/li]
[/list]

