[size=14pt][b][color=#9370DB]Genus-2 Jacobian VDF Mining Whitepaper[/color][/b][/size]

[b]NEW:[/b] We've published a comprehensive whitepaper on our innovative mining algorithm!

[b]"Genus-2 Jacobian VDF Mining: A Post-Quantum Resistant Proof-of-Work Algorithm"[/b]

[b]Key Innovations:[/b]
[list]
[li][b]Genus-2 Hyperelliptic Curves[/b] - 3-bit/element information density vs 1-bit/element for elliptic curves[/li]
[li][b]Mumford Representation[/b] - Efficient divisor class arithmetic[/li]
[li][b]Wesolowski Proof Protocol[/b] - Verifiable delay function with O(log T) verification[/li]
[li][b]Post-Quantum Security[/b] - 128/192/256-bit security levels against quantum attacks[/li]
[li][b]ASIC Resistance[/b] - Memory-hard computation prevents specialized hardware dominance[/li]
[/list]

[b]Security Analysis:[/b]
[code]
Classical Security:
- DLP Complexity: O(p^(4/9)) vs O(sqrt(p)) for elliptic curves
- Index calculus attacks significantly harder

Quantum Security:
- Shor's algorithm still applies, but...
- Security parameter chosen for post-quantum resilience
- PQ128: 256-bit curve for 128-bit post-quantum security
- PQ192: 384-bit curve for 192-bit post-quantum security
- PQ256: 512-bit curve for 256-bit post-quantum security
[/code]

[b]Download Whitepaper:[/b] [url=https://quillon.xyz/papers/genus2-jacobian-vdf-mining-whitepaper.pdf]genus2-jacobian-vdf-mining-whitepaper.pdf[/url]

